cs1302.calc

Class ReversePolishNotation

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs1302.calc.ReversePolishNotation

  • public class ReversePolishNotation
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains static methods for working with the Reverse Polish Notation of certain mathematical expressions. The following binary operations are supported: addition (+), subtraction (-), multiplication (*), division(/), and exponentiation (^). Note that ^ is used here for exponentiation and not bitwise exclusive OR (as is the case for ^ in Java) The following unary operations are supported: factorial (!).

    • Method Detail

      • infixToPostfix

        public static java.lang.String[] infixToPostfix(java.lang.String[] infix)
        Converts an expression expressed in infix notation as an array of Strings to the appropriate expression expressed in postfix notationan as an array of Strings.

        Here is an example of an expression in infix notation: 4 ! + 2 / 3 - 7 * 2 ^ 3 Each element of this expression would be an element in the array that is passed into this method.

        The resulting postfix expression is: 4 ! 2 3 / + 7 2 3 ^ * - Each element of this expression would be an element in the array that is returned by this method.

        Parameters:
        infix - an array containing an infix expression
        Returns:
        an array containing the postfix expression
